  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of this study is to evaluate the therapeutic efficacy of a neuromodulation technique,
      tDCS (transcranial direct current stimulation) used as a complementary treatment on negative
      symptoms. 60 patients will be randomized into two groups (active tDCS vs sham tDCS) and will
      be assessed after the intervention, 1 and 3 months after.Secondary outcomes shall include
      neuropsychological assessment, general symptomatology, extrapyramidal symptoms and social
      functioning.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
